Loud Like Love is the seventh studio album from internationally acclaimed rock band, Placebo. Recorded in London at RAK Studios during 2012 and early 2013, the album was produced by Adam Noble and features 10 brand new studio tracks.
Placebo has, to date, recorded six studio albums and sold more than 12 million records worldwide.  Their dark and melodic trademark sound featuring singer Brian Molko's instantly recognizable vocals has become one of the strongest brands in rock over the past decade.
